Caylen was not trying to say that might makes right.  What Caylen was trying to say is that <!--EZCODE HTML START--> <h2>Might is not automatically wrong, either.</h2><!--EZCODE HTML END--><br>
Just because the other guy has more guys, or higher levels, or can assemble faster than you, does not mean by default that the mob should be yours!  Everyone roots for the underdog in these arguments, but all too often the underdog is wrong -- and no one cares, because he's the underdog!<br>
<br>
