<br>
- Honor is the domain of the strong. For survival often sets   aside such concepts.<br>
- Death before forsaking ones code<br>
- Respect those above you till they show that they are weak   and unfit to lead. Then remove them.<br>
- Protect those below you. They are weak yet fill needed   spaces and thus are usefull.<br>
- Punish failure quickly, brutaly and fairly. Do not show   weakness to ones lessers.<br>
- Truth is a point of view. If you are the strongest point   of view. Then you are the force of truth.<br>
- Those that stand in your way should be dispatched with   quick brutal precision and should stand as a testament of   your power.<br>
<br>
Remember though that honor is not the same to all people. The Japanese sense of honor is far different from an Irishman's sense of honor which is different from Knightly European honor. <br>
<br>
I don't know how many of you watched the newer Record of the Lodoss Wars but Ashram(yay!) &amp; Parn(boo!) are good examples of different styles of honor. <br>
<br>
One can only be true to ones personal code if one has one. Don't let others judge your honor in comparison to yours.<br>
<br>
If someone tries to force you to comply with an code of honor other then your own. Crush them brutaly as a example to others that might attempt the same. <p>Keshin Grimscale<br>
Trooper of Cabilis<br>
26 Seasons of Blood & War<br>Lizard Tank of Nine Realms
