<br>
You are absolutely correct.  There are many different kinds of honor.  I should have specified that it is the code that I as a player follow, regardless of the ethics of any one particular character.<br>
<br>
The code that I follow as a RPGer has been culled from over a decade of gaming, first D&amp;D (back when &quot;Elf&quot; was a Class), then various padded-foam-weapon fantasy LARPs, then White Wolf LARPs, amongst others.  It is the way that I have found to ensure that not only do I have my own fun, but that I do not ruin the fun of most others in the game.<br>
<br>
Thank you for expressing your own code.  Now I shall know what to expect should I ever be in the vicinity of you and your guild, for presumably they approve of your code, even if they do not share it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> en masse</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And I shall know to walk the other way.<br>
